				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">neslib is just a subset the default cc65 NES runtime.<br /><br />Of course Shiru won't fix it, it's not his code.</div><br />No, shiru's neslib includes a lot of stuff of his own that is useful for game development, and the problems in question are definitely with code that he wrote.<br /><br />...which he wrote with the assumption that an 8-bit return type means only A is relevant to the return value, but apparently CC65 doesn't have such a convention and all return values are 16-bit. Hence, bugs that manifest only in specific situations (e.g. where the return value is immediately promoted to int).<br /><br />I made that assumption myself too, but I was lucky that I mostly used void functions, and the cases where I didn't were luckily never used in promotion.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

